-- Bezeq Falls to Lowest This Month on Report Regulation Won’t Ease
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-03-20T14:11:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/bezeq-falls-to-lowest-this-month-on-report-regulation-won-t-ease.html
Bezeq Israeli Telecommunication
Corp. (BEZQ)  declined to the lowest this month after TheMarker reported
the communication ministry won’t ease regulation on
the country’s largest fixed-line operator.  The  shares  fell 3.2 percent 6.12 shekels, the lowest level
since Feb. 29, at 4 p.m. in Tel Aviv.  The ministry will recommend the continued supervision on
rates and structural separation, TheMarker reported, without
saying where it got the information. Yechiel Shabi, a spokesman
for the ministry, declined to comment on the report.  Internet Gold-Golden Lines Ltd. (IGLD) , which through its B
Communications Ltd. unit holds a controlling interest in Bezeq,
declined 5.4 percent to 25.31 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
